        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Findeth a good thing",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " — A singular blessing; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and obtaineth favour of the Lord — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Obtaineth her, not by his own wisdom, or art, or endeavours, merely or chiefly, but by God’s good providence toward him, which orders that and all other events as it pleases him. The LXX. and Vulgate read at the end of this verse, “He that putteth away a good wife, putteth away a good thing; but he who retains an adulteress is foolish and wicked.”",
        "children": []
      },
